        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add auto fast mode cutoff",
        "body": "Fixes #85087\n\n## Summary\n\n- adds `fast: auto` alongside `fast: on/off`, with the default 60s cutoff and configurable `fast_seconds` plumbing\n- switches provider/app-server fast handling to a dynamic resolver so retries/continuations after the cutoff run without priority/fast tier where the backend can retier\n- emits channel-visible fast progress notices for long turns: `💨Fast: auto-off(...)` mid-turn and `💨Fast: auto-on` after reset\n- updates TUI/UI/ACP/protocol/docs/tests for the new auto mode\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm docs:list`\n- `node scripts/format-docs.mjs --check`\n- `node --import tsx scripts/control-ui-i18n.ts check`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node scripts/check-changed.mjs`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/openai-stream-wrappers.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/minimax-stream-wrappers.test.ts extensions/anthropic/stream-wrappers.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/extra-params.sampling.test.ts src/acp/translator.session-rate-limit.test.ts src/agents/fast-mode.test.ts`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/xai/stream.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-run.media-only.test.ts src/tui/tui-command-handlers.test.ts src/tui/commands.test.ts`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.test.ts`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run.fast-mode-auto.test.ts`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts -t \"fast auto progress\"`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: `fast: auto` starts a turn in fast mode, flips the runtime resolver off after the 60s threshold, emits channel-visible `💨Fast: auto-off(...)`, and resets with a post-turn fast progress notice.\n\nReal environment tested: local managed Gateway LaunchAgent on AlexM5, Gateway pid `62374`, CLI/Gateway `2026.5.20`, Telegram plugin enabled/configured/running in polling mode, bound Telegram DM `agent:main:telegram:direct:139745434`, real provider `openai-codex/gpt-5.5` through Codex app-server.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\npnpm build\npnpm openclaw gateway restart\npnpm openclaw gateway status --deep\npnpm openclaw channels status --deep --channel telegram\npnpm openclaw gateway call chat.send --json --params '{\n  \"sessionKey\":\"agent:main:telegram:direct:139745434\",\n  \"message\":\"Before replying, run a shell command that waits 75 seconds and prints fast-auto-live-proof. After the command finishes, reply exactly: fast-auto-live-proof complete\",\n  \"fastMode\":\"auto\",\n  \"deliver\":true,\n  \"timeoutMs\":300000,\n  \"idempotencyKey\":\"fast-auto-live-20260522041430\"\n}'\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: proof screenshot: https://files.catbox.moe/2jdq8m.png; HTML proof artifact: https://files.catbox.moe/ztzc5s.html. The local Computer Use screenshot showed the Telegram SamMac chat rendering `💨Fast: auto-off(61s>60s)` before the final reply. Trajectory also recorded run `fast-auto-live-20260522041430`, provider `openai-codex/gpt-5.5`, bash tool duration `74966ms`, output `fast-auto-live-proof`, and message tool success `messageId=134`.\n\nObserved result after fix: Gateway delivered Telegram message ids `133`, `134`, and `135`; visible channel proof showed `💨Fast: auto-off(61s>60s)` during the 75s tool wait, then `fast-auto-live-proof complete` delivered through the Telegram message tool.\n\nWhat was not tested: broad `pnpm test-projects --changed origin/main` did not complete locally; Crabbox/Testbox proof was blocked because the selected local `crabbox`/`blacksmith` binary failed basic sanity checks or was unavailable on this machine. Per-call `fastModeAutoSeconds` is not part of `chat.send` params; live proof used the default 60s cutoff.\n",
